0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aClaudia Roth's work on Bobo-Dioulasso, a city of half a million residents in Burkina Faso, provides uniquely detailed insight into the evolving life-world of a West African urban population in one of the poorest countries in the world. Closely documenting the livelihood strategies of members of various neighbourhoods, Roth’s work calls into question established notions of “the African family” as a solidary network, documents changing marriage and kinship relations under the impact of a persistent economic crisis, and explores the increasingly precarious social status of young women and men.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aCity and town lifezBurkina FasozBobo-Dioulasso. 0aFamilieszBurkina FasozBobo-Dioulasso. 0aSociology, UrbanzBurkina FasozBobo-Dioulasso. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aJong, Willemijn de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJong, Willemijn de, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPerlik, Manfred, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRoth, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoth, Claudia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSteuer, Noemi, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311099811540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781785333774?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781785333774423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781785333774/original  a978-3-11-099811-5  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL 